@qrkourier wrote:
> I'm trying to figure out whether the best workaround is to do rclone sync --ignore-checksum once to obtain a copy of all files and delete the removed files, and then drop the movie part of those images in Photos and try again.

I think a sync with `--ignore-checksum` just once will be enough.  Then rclone will just check the size and modtime and ignore the checksums after that.
